This document describes the process of compiling a vipg-simulator suite
release.

1. Ubuntu packages you need to have before installing the vipg project:
sudo apt-get install git-core swig g++ libc6-dev-i386 g++-multilib scons python-dev autoconf libtool m4 zlib1g-dev

2. Installing
./install

3. if mcpat does not build correctly then go into mcpat folder and type:
autoreconf --force --install
./configure
make

then try again
